<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Http_UserAgent_Mobile matches user-agent strings containing " ppc". This pattern incorrectly matches Macintosh desktops running on PowerPC processors. A quick and easy fix will continue to match most mobile user agents containing " ppc" because they usually have a trailing semicolon, something the Mac PowerPC user-agents do not. So adding a semicolon to the " ppc" pattern to change it to " ppc;" will produce more accurate results and will correctly NOT match Macs on PowerPC processors.</p>

<p>A quick "googleing" of user-agents containing " ppc" shows that all mobile user-agents with " ppc" also match " ppc;" whereas all Macs on PowerPC processors do not match " ppc;"</p>

